- (required) `reference_architectures/codex-saas/design/playbook/contract_declarations_v1.yaml`

**Steps:**
- Read cross-plane boundary BND-CP-AP-01 CP-side contract requirements.
- Scaffold CP-side contract provider surfaces and payload contracts.
- Align CP provider semantics with policy evaluation and tenant-context requirements.
- Keep CP contract surface stable for AP consumer and assembler closure.
- Document CP-side boundary semantics for downstream integration tasks.

**Definition of Done:**
- CP-side contract scaffold exists for boundary BND-CP-AP-01 with stable interface semantics.
- CP contract shape aligns with CP policy evaluation surface and AP consumer expectations.
- Semantic Acceptance (CAF-TCTX-01/Q-CPAP-TENANT-CARRIER-01/auth_claim/cp_ap_tenant_context_carrier_realization): CPâ†”AP contract handling and runtime wiring preserve the adopted tenant-context carrier explicitly across the boundary.
- Semantic Acceptance (CAF-TCTX-01/Q-CPAP-TENANT-CARRIER-01/auth_claim/cp_ap_tenant_context_carrier_realization): Boundary assumptions, contract language, and runtime composition remain coherent with the adopted tenant-context carrier.
- Semantic Acceptance (CAF-TCTX-01/Q-CPAP-TCTX-CONFLICT-01/claim_over_header/tenant_context_conflict_precedence_realization): Boundary and runtime handling apply the adopted tenant-context precedence rule consistently when more than one carrier is present.
- Semantic Acceptance (CAF-TCTX-01/Q-CPAP-TCTX-CONFLICT-01/claim_over_header/tenant_context_conflict_precedence_realization): Conflict handling remains explicit and coherent across CPâ†”AP contracts, boundary logic, and runtime composition.
- Semantic Acceptance (CAF-PLANE-01/Q-CP-AP-SURFACE-01/mixed/cp_ap_contract_surface_realization): Contract and runtime wiring surfaces realize the adopted CPâ†”AP contract surface consistently across the boundary.
- Semantic Acceptance (CAF-PLANE-01/Q-CP-AP-SURFACE-01/mixed/cp_ap_contract_surface_realization): Control/Application interaction semantics remain explicit and coherent with the adopted boundary shape through runtime wiring.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-CPAP-TENANT-CARRIER-01-auth_claim): Tenant context from a verified auth claim inside the Authorization credential (for example a JWT `tenant_id` claim), not from client-supplied tenant headers.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-CPAP-TCTX-CONFLICT-01-claim_over_header): Verified claim wins; reject if any other carrier conflicts.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-PLANE-01-Q-CP-AP-SURFACE-01-mixed): Mix: sync for enforcement, async for lifecycle and audit.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-CONTRACT-BND-CP-AP-01-CP): Scaffold the CP side of the material BND-CP-AP-01 contract boundary.

