- Preserve decision visibility for auth_claim carrier, policy, and runtime contract options.
- Keep option anchors deterministic so compiled obligations can bind to worker tasks.
- Avoid introducing new decisions; reflect adopted choices exactly as resolved.
- Expose stable option traces for downstream semantic acceptance enrichment.

**Definition of Done:**
- Adopted option anchors are present and unambiguous for compiled option obligations.
- Decision trace coverage remains deterministic and reproducible across re-runs.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-AP-TENANT-CARRIER-01-auth_claim): Tenant context from a verified auth claim inside the Authorization credential (for example a JWT `tenant_id` claim), not from client-supplied tenant headers.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-CPAP-TENANT-CARRIER-01-auth_claim): Tenant context from a verified auth claim inside the Authorization credential (for example a JWT `tenant_id` claim), not from client-supplied tenant headers.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-TCTX-01-Q-CPAP-TCTX-CONFLICT-01-claim_over_header): Verified claim wins; reject if any other carrier conflicts.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-MTEN-01-Q-MTEN-ISO-MODE-01-hybrid_tiered): Hybrid isolation (selective and tiered by tenant).
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-PLANE-01-Q-CP-AP-SURFACE-01-mixed): Mix: sync for enforcement, async for lifecycle and audit.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-AI-01-Q-AI-PART-01-cp_governs_ap_enforces): Control Plane governs policy; Application Plane enforces at runtime.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-COMP-01-Q-CAF-COMP-01-01-stream_plus_immutable_store): Use an event stream plus an immutable store (preferred for audit readiness).
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-AIOBS-01-Q-CAF-AIOBS-01-01-trace_metadata): Include structured trace metadata (no full reasoning content).
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-POL-02-Q-POL-DIST-01-cp_central_decision_ap_enforces): Control Plane centralizes policy decision; Application Plane enforces.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-IAM-02-Q-CAF-IAM-02-01-verified_token_claims): Propagate identity and tenant context via verified token claims at ingress.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-COMP-02-Q-CAF-COMP-02-01-warn_then_gate): Warn during scaffolding; fail closed at gate checks if unresolved.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-EXT-BACKEND_FOR_FRONTEND_BFF-Q-EXT-BFF-01-thin_facade_only): Thin BFF focused on auth/session/context and minor shaping; minimal aggregation.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-EXT-CIRCUIT_BREAKER-Q-EXT-CB-01-client_side_library): Circuit breaker enforced in client/SDK/library at call sites.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-CAF-POL-01-Q-AP-POLICY-POINTS-01-gate_all_ops): Gate all CRUD operations.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-EXT-API_GATEWAY-Q-EXT-API-GW-01-shared_gateway_and_services): Default: implement the gateway inside the Control Plane ingress boundary (no standalone gateway product). CP enforces baseline policies; services enforce additional policies with explicit boundaries.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-OPT-EXT-AUDITABILITY-Q-EXT-AUDIT-01-security_plus_admin_actions): Audit security events plus privileged admin/operator actions.
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-AUTH-MOCK-01-boundary-adapter): Materialize the AP auth-context adapter that resolves the mock Authorization/Bearer contract for HTTP boundaries. (TBP: TBP-AUTH-MOCK-01)
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-FASTAPI-01-composition-root): Materialize FastAPI composition root (TBP: TBP-FASTAPI-01)
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-FASTAPI-01-dependency-provider-boundary): Materialize FastAPI dependency provider boundary (TBP: TBP-FASTAPI-01)

