### TG-40-persistence-cp-policy â€” Implement CP persistence for policy (sqlalchemy_orm code_bootstrap)

- required_capability: `persistence_implementation`
- worker_id: `worker-persistence`
- depends_on: `TG-00-CP-runtime-scaffold`, `TG-35-policy-enforcement-core`

**Inputs (paths only; open as needed):**
- (required) `reference_architectures/codex-saas/spec/guardrails/profile_parameters_resolved.yaml`
- (required) `reference_architectures/codex-saas/design/playbook/system_domain_model_v1.yaml`

**Steps:**
- Implement CP persistence contracts for policy aggregate on sqlalchemy_orm rails.
- Keep persistence behavior aligned to code_bootstrap schema management strategy.
- Preserve policy-specific retention and audit consistency constraints.
- Separate CP persistence adapters from policy evaluation orchestration.
- Expose stable repository surfaces for runtime wiring and tests.

**Definition of Done:**
- CP persistence slice for policy uses sqlalchemy_orm semantics with governance-safe boundaries.
- Schema lifecycle assumptions remain compatible with code_bootstrap strategy.
- TBP Gate (TBP-PG-01/G-PG-PERSISTENCE-SEAM-REALIZATION): Persistence implementation realizes the resolved persistence seam and keeps storage interaction inside the persistence boundary for the selected rails.
- TBP Gate (TBP-PG-01/G-PG-PERSISTENCE-SEAM-REALIZATION): Repository logic is expressed through the declared persistence boundary and wiring surface so runtime composition can honor the resolved persistence strategy.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-ORM-REALIZATION): ORM-backed persistence realizes SQLAlchemy-owned runtime surfaces explicitly, including engine or session-opening helper adoption and mapped-model metadata ownership inside the persistence boundary.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-ORM-REALIZATION): Repository logic opens SQLAlchemy sessions through the role-bound shared runtime helper contract rather than treating a raw `sessionmaker` object as the request-scoped session context.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-ORM-REALIZATION): Shared runtime helpers, emitted runtime `.env`, and PostgreSQL env examples remain coherent for the accepted SQLAlchemy DATABASE_URL contract when ORM-backed postgres rails are resolved.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-SCHEMA-STRATEGY-ALIGNMENT): When schema management is code_bootstrap, SQLAlchemy metadata/bootstrap remains ORM-owned, imports or registers mapped model modules before `create_all`, and any role-bound shared helper stays infrastructural rather than acting as the cross-plane bootstrap owner.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-SCHEMA-STRATEGY-ALIGNMENT): When schema management is code_bootstrap, the application-plane runtime composition root invokes an AP-owned ORM bootstrap entrypoint before serving AP traffic.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-SCHEMA-STRATEGY-ALIGNMENT): When schema management is code_bootstrap, the control-plane runtime composition root invokes a CP-owned ORM bootstrap entrypoint before serving CP traffic.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-SCHEMA-STRATEGY-ALIGNMENT): When schema management is code_bootstrap, repository factories and request-scoped handlers do not own unsynchronized lazy schema bootstrap as the primary realization path; any fallback convergence stays secondary to startup ownership.
- TBP Gate (TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01/G-SQLALCHEMY-SCHEMA-STRATEGY-ALIGNMENT): When schema management uses migrations, runtime persistence code avoids silently creating schema and remains compatible with migration-owned evolution.
- Compiled Obligation (OBL-CP-ENTITY-POLICY-PERSISTENCE): Provide control-plane persistence surfaces for the Policy aggregate.
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01-runtime-module): Materialize the role-bound shared SQLAlchemy runtime module (engine/session factory) for ORM-backed persistence. (TBP: TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01)
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01-metadata-module): Materialize the framework-legible shared SQLAlchemy metadata/base surface used by ORM-backed repositories and plane-owned bootstrap entrypoints. (TBP: TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01)
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01-ap-schema-bootstrap): Materialize the application-plane SQLAlchemy schema bootstrap entrypoint aligned to the resolved schema management strategy. (TBP: TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01)
- Compiled Obligation (O-TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01-cp-schema-bootstrap): Materialize the control-plane SQLAlchemy schema bootstrap entrypoint aligned to the resolved schema management strategy. (TBP: TBP-SQLALCHEMY-01)

