+# Task Report - TG-90-runtime-wiring
+
+## Summary
+Materialized compose-first runtime assembly for CP/AP/UI/Postgres, closed AP interface bindings at the composition boundary, and emitted binding closure evidence artifacts.
+
+## Inputs consumed
+- `reference_architectures/codex-saas/spec/guardrails/profile_parameters_resolved.yaml`
+  - Used deployment stack identity (`deployment.stack_name: codex-saas`), compose packaging posture, runtime ports, mock-auth, and SQLAlchemy/Postgres rails.
+- `reference_architectures/codex-saas/spec/guardrails/tbp_resolution_v1.yaml`
+  - Used selected TBP obligations for compose/runtime wiring and UI packaging/proxy surfaces.
+- `reference_architectures/codex-saas/design/playbook/interface_binding_contracts_v1.yaml`
+  - Used assembler-owned bindings for `BIND-AP-*` contracts to produce explicit closure evidence under `caf/binding_reports/`.
+- `node tools/caf/resolve_tbp_role_bindings_v1.mjs codex-saas --capability runtime_wiring`
+  - Used role-binding path/evidence expectations for compose, dockerfiles, `.env`, `.gitignore`, and UI proxy artifacts.
+
+## Files created or modified
+- `code/ap/application/services.py`
+- `docker/compose.candidate.yaml`
+- `docker/Dockerfile.ap`
+- `docker/Dockerfile.cp`
+- `docker/Dockerfile.ui`
+- `docker/nginx.ui.conf`
+- `.env`
+- `.gitignore`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-activity_events.yaml`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-collection_memberships.yaml`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-collection_permissions.yaml`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-collections.yaml`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-tenant_role_assignments.yaml`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-widget_versions.yaml`
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-widgets.yaml`
+
+## Claims
+- AP composition wiring now binds resource service facades to persistence-backed access ports (no production in-memory fallback selected at assembly time).
+- Compose runtime topology is materialized at `docker/compose.candidate.yaml` with explicit `cp`, `ap`, `ui`, and `postgres` service roles.
+- Stateful support service startup uses health-gated dependency wiring (`depends_on.postgres.condition: service_healthy`) for CP/AP.
+- Runtime config is externalized through `.env` and compose `env_file`, with container-local DB DSNs using compose DNS (`postgres`) and host-local `.env` defaults preserved.
+- CP/AP dockerfiles install dependencies from canonical repo-root `requirements.txt` rather than inline package lists.
+- UI packaging/wiring is materialized via a multi-stage Node->nginx container and nginx proxy routes for `/api` and `/cp`.
+- Interface binding contracts assembled by `TG-90-runtime-wiring` are explicitly evidenced as closed in `caf/binding_reports/*.yaml`.
+
+## How to validate
+- Inspect `docker/compose.candidate.yaml` for:
+  - top-level `name: codex-saas`
+  - service objects (`cp`, `ap`, `ui`, `postgres`) under `services:`
+  - `env_file` usage and container-local `DATABASE_URL` values for CP/AP
+  - postgres healthcheck and CP/AP `depends_on` health conditions.
+- Inspect `code/ap/application/services.py` to confirm `build_default_resource_service_facade_registry()` resolves providers via `build_access_port_registry()`.
+- Inspect `.env` and `.gitignore` for TBP role-binding evidence strings (`CAF_CONTAINER_RUNTIME_CMD`, `DATABASE_URL`, `.env`, `*.local`).
+- Inspect `docker/Dockerfile.ui` and `docker/nginx.ui.conf` for UI build+proxy contract lines (`node`, `npm`, `nginx`, `npm run build`, `proxy_pass` to `ap:8000` and `cp:8001`).
+- Inspect `caf/binding_reports/*.yaml` for `schema_version: caf_interface_binding_report_v1`, `status: closed`, and non-empty consumer/provider/assembler evidence paths.
+- Optional manual runtime check: `docker compose -f docker/compose.candidate.yaml up --build`.
+
+## Known limitations
+- Runtime wiring is candidate-quality for local compose execution only; production hardening and deployment posture are out of scope.
+- Host-side frontend build commands were not executed in-task; UI build is owned by container packaging surfaces.
+
+## Evidence anchors
+- `code/ap/application/services.py` - AP composition binding closure to persistence providers.
+- `docker/compose.candidate.yaml` - compose topology, service roles, env externalization, health-gated startup.
+- `docker/Dockerfile.ap` / `docker/Dockerfile.cp` - canonical `requirements.txt` installation for CP/AP.
+- `docker/Dockerfile.ui` and `docker/nginx.ui.conf` - UI containerization and AP/CP proxy wiring.
+- `.env` and `.gitignore` - runtime env contract and local-secret ignore posture.
+- `caf/binding_reports/BIND-AP-*.yaml` - explicit interface-binding closure evidence artifacts.
