--- /dev/null
+++ b/companion_repositories/codex-saas/profile_v1/caf/reviews/TG-90-runtime-wiring.md
@@ -0,0 +1,54 @@
+# Review Note - TG-90-runtime-wiring
+
+| check_id | PASS/FAIL | Evidence |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| RR-PY-SEC-01 | PASS | Runtime wiring uses env-driven config (`.env`, compose env) and does not introduce unsafe execution primitives. |
+| RR-PY-CORR-01 | PASS | AP composition now resolves providers through `build_access_port_registry()` in `code/ap/application/services.py`. |
+| RR-PY-CORR-01A | PASS | Shared imports remain module-root coherent (`code.ap...` imports `code.common...` and persistence modules correctly). |
+| RR-PY-CORR-02 | PASS | No broken AP/CP import wiring introduced by runtime assembly edits. |
+| RR-PY-PERF-01 | PASS | Runtime wiring changes are configuration/composition oriented; no pathological runtime loops introduced. |
+| RR-TST-BLOCK-01 | PASS | Task report provides deterministic manual validation for compose/runtime and binding evidence. |
+| RR-TST-HIGH-01 | PASS | Runtime surfaces are verifiable through file-level inspection and optional compose smoke run. |
+| RR-TST-HIGH-02 | PASS | Changes keep coupling explicit at composition boundaries (no hidden fallback wiring). |
+| RR-COMP-CORR-01 | PASS | `docker/compose.candidate.yaml` defines valid service objects with coherent build and runtime wiring. |
+| RR-COMP-BUILD-01 | PASS | CP/AP Dockerfiles install from canonical `requirements.txt`; UI Dockerfile uses explicit package install/build steps. |
+| RR-COMP-RDY-01 | PASS | Compose includes `postgres` healthcheck and CP/AP health-gated startup dependencies. |
+| RR-COMP-SEC-01 | PASS | Secrets are externalized to `.env`; compose/service config does not hardcode credentials in code modules. |
+| RR-FA-CORR-01 | PASS | FastAPI service runtime entrypoints remain coherent (`code.ap.main:app`, `code.cp.main:app`). |
+| RR-FA-SEC-01 | PASS | Auth/tenant semantics remain enforced in existing AP/CP boundaries; runtime wiring does not bypass them. |
+| RR-FA-BOUNDARY-ERR-01 | PASS | Existing AP/CP error-handling boundaries remain intact. |
+| RR-FA-SCHEMA-BOOTSTRAP-01 | PASS | Schema bootstrap hooks remain in CP/AP startup paths; runtime wiring preserves them. |
+| RR-FA-ARCH-01 | PASS | AP/CP boundary responsibilities remain explicit with compose wiring aligned to declared planes. |
+| RR-SPA-WIRE-01 | PASS | UI service is wired in compose and reverse-proxied to AP via `/api` route. |
+| RR-SPA-WIRE-02 | PASS | UI API contract paths remain compatible with proxy surface (`/api/...` to AP). |
+| RR-SPA-WIRE-03 | PASS | AP-backed UI pages retain backend reachability via nginx proxy configuration. |
+| RR-SPA-STATE-01 | PASS | Runtime-wiring changes do not regress SPA state shape or route behavior. |
+| RR-SPA-ERR-DETAIL-01 | PASS | UI error-detail behavior in `code/ui/src/api.js` remains unchanged and compatible. |
+| RR-SPA-FORM-01 | PASS | Mock auth persona/header contract remains explicit and unchanged by runtime wiring. |
